<blockquote>
<p>I see, how exactly would I go about fixing this?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Compose your command sequence so you won’t be scheduling instances of commands that require the same subsystems as the groups running your paths.</p>
<p>Here’s a <a href="https://bovlb.github.io/frc-tips/commands/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">good reference with visuals on commands and their lifecycles</a>.  Then you can look at the <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-compositions.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">various composition methods from wpilib</a>.</p>
